@startuml

title WAL Storage Sector Alignment

note as UnalignedIssue #FFE6E6
**Unaligned Write Problem**
• A write starts in the middle of a sector
• It spans partial 512-byte boundaries
• Storage must do Read-Modify-Write cycles
• Existing bytes must be read before writing
• Throughput drops sharply
end note

note as AlignedSolution #E6FFE6
**Aligned Write Solution**
• Start the write at a sector boundary
• Overwrite complete sectors only
• No Read-Modify-Write needed
• Hardware can write directly
• Performance becomes more predictable
end note

note as PaddingStrategy #F0F8FF
**Padding Strategy**
• Add structured padding to reach boundaries
• Use markers and lengths so recovery can detect padding
• Tiny space overhead buys large performance gains
• Especially valuable for append-only WAL workloads
end note

note bottom #FFFFCC
**Storage Fundamental**
Disks and SSDs write complete sectors atomically.
WAL design works better when append boundaries respect that reality.
end note

@enduml
